  "narrative_arc": "Black girl who prays for blue eyes because she has internalized white beauty standards as a survival strategy. Morrison documents how racism enters through aesthetics — through Dick-and-Jane readers, through Shirley Temple cups, through every cultural message that says Black is ugly. Raped by her father, she retreats into madness.",
  "why_this_character_matters": "Pecola's dome maps how cultural violence (Layer 11 — Creativity/Identity) can destroy a person more thoroughly than any institutional system. Her dome would show thin institutional layers but devastated human layers.",
